The newly built Braamfischerville primary school in Soweto, which opened on Wednesday, has been named Nomzamo Madikizela-Mandela Primary School. Named after struggle icon Winnie Madikizela-Mandela, it is a fully functional smart school equipped with smartboards and tablets. The school has 33 classrooms. . Each classroom has a capacity of 40 learners, and the school can cater for a maximum of 1 320 learners. Excited parents and children in new school uniforms converged on the school on Wednesday morning. Infrastructure and Development MEC Jacob Mamebulo urged community members to look after the facility. Mamebulo handed the keys of the school, built at a cost of R83 million, to Gauteng MEC of education Panyaza Lesufi. Lesufi said the Gauteng education department plans to open a school in the province every month this year.